Pages 60 through 121 in the annotated slide deck cover Jython hosting Scala.

To compile ScalaUtils.scala:

scalac ScalaUtils.scala

To package the classes generated by the above compilation process into scala-utils.jar so Jython can easily access them:

jar -cf scala-utils.jar ScalaUtils*.class

To run demo.py:

path/to/jython -Dpython.path=scala-utils.jar demo.py

To use the interactive Jython console (with access to the ScalaUtils library)

/path/to/jython -Dpython.path=scala-utils.jar 

Sample console session:

>>> from scalathon import scalafy
>>> from ScalaUtils import *
>>> 
>>> def python_age(age):
...     return age / 2.8
... 
>>> 
>>> ageGroupMethod(21.0)
2
>>> ageGroupFunction = ageGroupFunction()
>>> ageGroupFunction.apply(21.0)
2
>>
>>> ages = ages()
>>> scalafied_python_age=scalafy(python_age)
>>> 
>>> python_ages = ages.mapValues(scalafied_python_age)
>>> python_ages
Map(Python -> 7.500000000000001, Scala -> 3.2142857142857144)
>>>
>>> python_age_group_function = reptileAgeGroupFunctionFactory(scalafied_python_age)
>>> python_age_group = python_age_group_function.apply(21.0)
>>> python_age_group
1 
